"The user begins by browsing View 1 at the [Overview] level to observe the overall distribution of players' fantasy points and match outcomes. Next, they select a range of fantasy points on the x-axis in View 1, causing View 2 to filter for associated player statistics at the [Exploration] level. Then, the user toggles between batting and bowling metrics in View 2 and drills into individual matches in View 3 at the [Detail] level to focus on extreme performances for runs scored or wickets taken. Finally, highlighted match IDs from View 3 are passed to View 4 at the [Insight] level to uncover broader impacts of player contributions on match results and team victories, visualized through aggregated metrics like boundaries and player-of-match effects."